Package: TreeIndex
Type: Package
Title: R package to manage tree hierarchies
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c( 
          person("Jayaram", "Kancherla", email="jayaram.kancherla@gmail.com", role=c("aut")),
          person("Justin", "Wagner", email="jwagner@cs.umd.edu", role=c("aut")),
          person("Hector", "Corrada Bravo", email="hcorrada@gmail.com", role=c("aut", "cre"))
          )
Maintainer: Hector Corrada Bravo <hcorrada@gmail.com>
Description: This package provides the TreeIndex class to support interactive data
          visualization of datasets with tree hierarchies. The TreeIndex object provides methods to
          split the tree at a certain level or given a node selection. The result of a 
          split is a list of nodes and indices that can be used aggregate counts.
